## Main Stories
1.  Government Champions Sport as Vital for National Development
    Minister Elvis Nkandu emphasised that sport is crucial for Zambia's progress, promoting citizen health, fostering social cohesion, and generating jobs through its growing economic contribution, as highlighted during the Vivo Energy-sponsored North vs South Golf Challenge in Lusaka.
2.  Zesco United CAF Qualification Boosts Zambia's Continental Standing
    Coach Emmanuel Siwale declared Zesco United's qualification for the CAF Confederation Cup Group Stage after defeating Jwaneng Galaxy (5-4 aggregate) as a victory for Zambia, crucial in the nation's efforts to regain its previous allocation of four continental club competition slots.
3.  Zanaco Reclaims MTN Super League Summit
    Coach Mumamba Numba praised his Zanaco team's character after a 2-0 victory over Mutondo Stars propelled them back to the top of the MTN Super League table with 21 points, three points clear of second-placed Red Arrows, strengthening their title challenge.

